  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Chop your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half, then add them to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) with a generous drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>, then put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until slightly charred – these are your <strong>roasted tomatoes</strong></p><p>Once done, remove the tray[s] from the oven, transfer the <strong>roasted tomatoes</strong> to a plate and reserve the tray[s] for later</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1642171494699-x200.jpg",
